A small smoking device commonly made out of glass, ceramic, or metal. Dugouts are generally used by marijuana smokers to smoke marijuana in a more discrete manner (as many dugouts appear to look like ordinary filtered cigarettes) or by tobacco smokers who prefer to smoke a small amount of tobacco only.

Smoking material is 'loaded' on one end of the dugout, while the other end is placed between the lips like a cigarette. The user then uses matches or a lighter to burn the smoking material, producing smoke which is then inhaled.

